comm: beauty to start. 131 kph, full outside off. The ball moves away late and beats the bat of Warner. Superb delivery. Definite shape.
prods at that and gets a thick outside edge which dies down and gets Australia one to third man. Soft hands. Comes back in this time.

135 kph, Finch has chopped on. That movement again. Henry keeps this full, the ball moves back in. Finch doesn't care. He goes on with an exuberant on-the-up drive with his feet rooted in the crease. What that does is create a massive gap between bat and pad. The ball deviates in, takes the inside edge and clatters into leg stump. Not a great shot first ball. Excellent bowling from Henry. Just a little bit of movement, more than enough at this level.
ooh again. 137 kph, full but straighter. Smith looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge onto his pad
139 kph, on the pads and Smith tucks him through square leg for a couple. Good stroke.

138 kph, superb shot. But good signs for New Zealand. Some swing for Henry. Full and wide outside off, Smith leans forward and caresses his cover drive through the huge gap at cover. Superlative timing.
poor ball to start. 138 kph, a low full toss outside off. Warner needn't do much but just drive through cover. Four easy runs. Some swing in the air though, moving away
well bowled. 139 kph, full outside off, moves away again. Warner has a leaden-footed poke to cover.
good delivery, good leave. 139 kph, full and wide but moving away. Warner respectfully and rightly leaves
137 kph, full outside off. A bit of movement. Defended
good lines. 135 kph, outside off. Warner defends into the off side, towards cover
excellent over save the first ball. Good length outside off, forces Warner to let that one go
overpitched, 135 kph. Full outside off, quite the ideal line to Smith who shuffles across. A mis-timed drive finds mid-off
good length outside off, 136 kph, blocked
on the pads again. A couple more to Smith as he nudges it through square leg. Can't stray there to Smith
138 kph, excellent lines. Just outside off, Smith stays in the crease and is rapped on the pads. An optimistic appeal
good length on a fourth-stump line, defended back
139 kph, back of a length on off, worked away to square leg
another good delivery. Full outside off, shapes away but Warner lets it go. Good leave
136 kph, full length around middle, worked to mid-on.
139 kph, a good length again close to off. Cut to point
138 kph, strays down leg, goes wide of the crease. No swing on that occasion. A wide
142 kph, good length outside off, patted down to Guptill at point
142 kph, another tight delivery. Full outside off, defended towards point
on the pads, 137 kph. Swings away late. Warner finds mid-on with a push. Just the wide off the over
nicely bowled. Full outside off, not much swing. Left alone
135 kph, ooh. Back of a length outside off, the ball moves away late. Bounces extra. And beats the bat of Smith. But not his arm. Thuds into that back arm.
139 kph, a half-volley on off, worked away to mid-on
140 kph, a yorker on off. Driven to mid-on
139 kph, a bouncer. Too short from Henry, way over the head. Called.
138 kph, another back of a length delivery outside off. Smith stays in his crease and keeps the ball down. Good pace
on off stump, which is leg side-ish for Smith. Worked down to fine leg
pushed away this time. Excellent bowling. Left alone
good length outside off, 139 kph. Punched to extra cover from the crease
143 kph, good length outside off, defended into the off side
good length outside off, another punchy drive to extra cover
140 kph, good length on off, worked to square leg
good over again. Another maiden. Full delivery outside off, Smith gets across and blocks
through the off side this time. Back of a length outside off, Warner gets on top of the bounce and guides it through point for three.
reads the length early and pulls it away over square leg. Slightly short and Smith jumps all over it. Doesn't keep it down, intentionally. Nice stroke
full delivery outside off, comes back in. Smith defends the ball into his front pad and the ball trickles backwards
135 kph, full on the pads, worked to mid-on
135 kph, on the pads, Smith misses a flick. Struck on the thigh pad. A leg bye ensues
excellent line. Good length on off, blocked to point

dropped! That is not an easy catch. May have saved three. Full but way down the leg, Smith gets across and just gets a bit of bat on his flick. Watling dives to his left but can only get fingertips on that.
excellent running. Good length on off, inside-edged to deep square leg. The fielder has some distance to cover, allowing the second to be made easily
worked away to deep square leg again, just for one
back of a length outside off, pushed up to mid-off

how close is that? Is there some bat on that? Umpire Martell says no. No bat. Full delivery outside off, the ball swings back in, not prodigiously but enough. Beats Smith and hits him on the pad just outside off. Looked a good decision.
good length outside off, blocked
137 kph, good length on middle and leg, Warner is surprised by some extra bounce but fends
bouncer on off, Warner pulls but the ball goes over the pull
shot! Full outside off, Warner walks across and flicks him away through midwicket with nonchalant ease. In the air but in the gap
fullish delivery outside off, left alone
good single. 137 kph, good length outside off, a thick inside edge towards square leg

over the boundary. Picks the length early again. Good length just outside off, the ball sits up for Smith who pulls merrily over square leg. The ball has enough on it to just clear the boundary. No risk in that stroke
147 kph, full outside off. Warner clears his front leg and drills his drive back past mid-off. Disdain
150.4 kph. Overpitched outside off, driven to short cover. Races away to the fielder, good stop
149.6 kph, back of a length outside off, cuts Warner in half as he misses his push. Beat Warner for pace
149 kph, good length outside off, pushed away to extra cover
147 kph, short and dispatched. Warner stays in his crease and pulls over square leg. Was probably anticipating that length

148 kph, and Ferguson has a wicket in his first over in international cricket. Good length outside off, the ball moves away just a touch. Warner hangs his bat out, looking to get one down to third man. The ball takes the inside edge and hits the off stump. The second chop-on dismissal this afternoon. Another loose, lazy stroke. A bit of complacency in that shot
good length outside off, 122 kph, a bit of gentle away movement for de Grandhomme. Left alone
on the pads, poor delivery, worked down to fine leg
125 kph, full delivery outside off, good leave
a tad too full outside off, a mis-timed drive finds mid-off
124 kph, not very pacey but accurate. Close to off on a good length. Defended
126 kph, overpitched outside off, mis-times it again. May be the result of his accentuated closed stance. Can't get his hands through the line as easily, as fluently
151 kph, good length outside off, steered to third man
150 kph, good length outside off, pushed to cover
151 kph, a big appeal. Good length on off, the ball shapes back in. Bailey is beaten on the inside edge as the ball comes back in. Strikes Bailey just outside off.
150 ks again. cuts Bailey in half after missing a push
150 kph, good length outside off, a thick outside edge down to third man.
146 kph, short on off, pulled to deep square leg
nudged to fine leg
another inside edge. 127 kph, fullish delivery outside off, a thick inside edge juuuust misses off stump. Takes a bit of the stump mic on its way to fine leg
worked to fine leg. Poor lines
126 kph, good length on middle, worked away to deep square leg
a tad too full, driven through cover
a slow, short, nothing delivery on leg. Pulled down ti fine leg with so much ease
148 kph, good length on off, worked to fine leg. Ferguson has overstepped.
fantastic delivery. 148 kph, wide yorker. Bailey misses his glide. Beaten for pace
148 kph, good length outside off, Bailey pulls to deep square leg. Not quite timed
152 kph. Very quick but can't bowl there, full on Smith's pads, worked away through midwicket easily
147 kph, full outside off, defended
good length outside off, tapped back. Looked to go through the off side
149 kph, full and straight, pushed out to mid-on for one
125 kph, good length just outside off, a blotched push into the off side
128 kph, good length moving away. Guided to point from the crease
hmm, another inside edge. Short and wide outside off, Smith looks to cut but gets a thick edge to fine leg
full outside off, no stroke
126 kph, on the pads, nudged to deep square leg
128 kph, full on off, shovelled to midwicket
87 kph, full outside off, defended to cover. Not much turn
short and slow on off, worked to deep square leg. Easily clipped
better. Full and quick, pushed through. Defended back
uses his feet, comes down and defends. Well bowled again
sees Bailey coming and fires it in outside off, Bailey defends
short on the pads, pulled emphatically to deep square leg
123 kph, good length on off, pushed to mid-on
lovely stroke. Full and wide outside off, Bailey stays in his crease and lofts the ball easily over mid-off. Clears the short boundary.
good length on off, nudged away to deep square leg
a bit of shape. Full and wide, moving away. Guided to point
worked away to square leg
short and wide, a nothing delivery at 125 kph. The ball goes over the bat of Smith's cut
90 kph, tossed up outside off, driven down to mid-off
83 kph, worked away to midwicket from the back foot
pushed to long-off from the front foot
another simple nudge through midwicket for one
flatter and quicker on the pads, worked away to deep square leg for one more. Five singles off the over
short and wide, scythes to deep point
full delivery outside off, defended towards cover
133 kph, overpitched outside off, defended into the off side. Nice channel
134 kph, full on off, pushed to mid-on
after three good deliveries, Neesham dishes out one short and wide. Smith transfers his weight back and cuts past backward point. Made that look easy
on the pads, worked to midwicket. Bailey had to hustle through for one

umpire Dharmasena checking if it has carried. That looked like it did. The third umpire is being called. Soft signal is out. Bailey trudging off. Goes in cleanly. And that will be the end of Bailey. Quite a terrible delivery, full down leg. Bailey gets a little bit of bat on that, carries low to Watling's left who gets across and takes it with both hands. A lucky wicket for NZ.
134 kph, full and wide, slashed to deep point
134 kph, full outside off, Marsh lets this one go
airy. 132 kph, full and wide, Marsh gets down on one knee and caresses his drive but fails to keep it down. Through the cover region for one
full outside off, pushed to mid-off
135 kph, on the pads, worked away through midwicket for a run
139 kph, good length outside off, blocked towards point

gone! Marsh is run-out at the non-strikers end. Punches his bat in disgust. Full delivery on off, Smith drives it crisply and cleanly back at the bowler's right. Neesham mis-fields but gets his hands to the ball. It ricochets slightly but into the non-strikers stumps. Marsh was backing up and has been caught more than a few feet short of his crease
on the pads, worked to midwicket
on the pads, clipped to fine leg
134 kph, good length close to off, pushed towards cover
136 kph, overpitched outside off, drilled to mid-off on the up
132 kph, good length outside off, a flayed cut to point
140 kph, back of a length outside off, punched from the back foot to cover
fantastic lines. Close to off, defended back
short delivery on off, pulled through backward square leg for a couple more
fifty for Smith. Has been lucky, but has ensured he's made the runs. Full and wide, carved through cover point for a run
140 kph, back of a length on off, Head gets on top of the bounce and defends
141 kph, good length around off. Impeccable lines. Shovelled to square leg with a strong bottom hand
fullish on off, worked to midwicket
full on off, driven back to the bowler. Giving Smith nothing, great bowling
worked away to fine leg for one. Drags it from off stump
strays down leg, a free run, wide
full and wide outside off, Head goes after it but gets a thick inside edge which misses the stumps again
short outside off, dabbed down to third man for one. Australia's 100 up
a tad too full, driven to mid-off
146 kph, good length outside off, comes back in. Defended back
shortish and a touch of width. Punched to point from the crease
bouncer, loopy, outside off. Smith easily avoids it
144 kph, good length on off and middle, defended
145 kph, overpitched on off, driven back to the bowler
five runs. Short and wide from Ferguson. Smith cuts in front of point for four. On top of the bounce. Lovely stroke. A no ball too
slower ball, 118 kph, short outside off. Pulled over midwicket for a couple
through mid-on for four. Overpitched outside off, Head mis-times his drive, but a strong bottom hand takes the ball past mid-on for four
full and very wide, 135 kph. Head misses his cut. Wide
135 kph, full and close to off, defended into the off side
136 kph, worked away through backward square leg for a couple more. Good shot
another wide, 135 kph, down the leg side. Called

dropped. Henry drops a sitter. Oh my. Unusual. Full and wide outside off from Neesham. Head drives with bat well away from the pad. Hits it straight to Henry at mid-off, who looks to take it reverse-cupped catch. Bursts through his hands. Big moment in the game
another wide. Down leg, and Head misses his flick.
131 kph, back of a length on the pads. Head gets a bit of bat in his flick, races away to the fine leg boundary
good length around off, defended back. Straight face
good length outside off, 143 kph. Pushed to deep cover from the back foot. Nice shot
143 kph, good length outside off, Smith nudges this into the leg side
146.5 kph, good length close to off stump. Smith stays in his crease and defends
123 kph, slower ball on off. Driven back powerfully
full outside off, shovelled through square leg for one. Head looking to belt everything, a focus on power as opposed to  timing
132 kph, good length on off, pulled through square leg
138 kph, full and wide outside off, Head slashes and gets one to third man. Another no-ball, knocks the stumps down with his leg at the bolwer's end. Sloppy from NZ
short delivery on off, Smith backs away and swats his pull over mid-on for four
136 kph, close to off, defended
135 kph, full outside off, blocked into the off side
133 kph, overpitched outside off, driven through cover for a run
drops short and Smith hekps himself to four with a well-executed pull over midwicket. Simple batting basics
tossed up on leg, driven to long-on
short and wide, slapped to deep cover for a run
on the pads, 89 kph, worked to short fine leg
shortish outside off, cut to deep point
superb shot. Too full, rather wide. Caressed through cover with a sublime drive. Between cover and mid-off
137 kph, back of a length on off, pulled to deep square leg. On top of the bounce, kept down
good length outside off, 138 kph. Dabbed down to third man
137 kph, a crisp drive to cover
138 kph, lovely shot, back of a length down leg. Smith pulls it away through backward square leg with a lovely pull. Kept that down too, found the gap
good length outside off, 136 kph. Blocked
too full this time. Four more easy runs. Overpitched on middle, Smith on-drives perfectly through mid-on.
92 kph, tossed up outside off, driven to short cover
on the pads, flicked to midwicket
drops short again, hammered to deep square leg who does well, scurrying to his right. Latham
slow and on the pads, Smith misses his flick. Struck on the pad
slow through the air, full on off. Defended
shortish on the pads, worked to deep midwicket for one
on the pads again, worked down to fine leg
112 kph, full on off. Driven to mid-off
good length outside off, 123 kph. Dabbed to backward point
full and wide, slashed through the off side
full outside off, 125 kph, defended
lovely end. Full and straight, Smith blocks
flat on off and middle, skewed to short third man. Head sends his captain back just in time
90 kph, full on middle, driven back to the bowler
82 kph, short and wide outside off, slapped to deep cover
slow through the air, full on middle. Blocked. Excellent delivery, loopy
short on the pads, 83 kph. Flicked with the power in his wrists through deep square leg for a couple more
93 kph, flat outside off, carved towards point
118 kph, short and wide, and hammered. Lays into his cut through point, too much width from de Grandhomme
ooh, fullish and closer to off this time. Head wants one down to third man but the ball misses the bat
dabs one to third man, 123 kph. Good follow-up
127 kph, full delivery outside off, glided down towards point
127 ks, worked through square leg for a run
126 kph, short and wide again, hammered to deep point for one
tossed up on leg, driven back
94 kph, low full toss on the pads, Head flicks to midwicket. Should have done more with that
well bowled. 82 ks, slow outside off, nudged towards point
shortish and wide, Head hurries back and cuts to deep point.
loads of air on that, tosses that up, full on middle and leg, driven with ease to long-on for one
ooh, a streaky shot. Head comes down and looks to hit over cover but the ball stays low, takes the inside edge towards fine leg
back of a length on the pads, worked to deep square leg
135 kph, shortish outside off, pushed through point for a run
135 kph, good length on off, Head gets on top of the bounce and opens the face to get one down to third man
no no no. Another no-ball. Humongous no-ball. Overstepped. Short on off, pulled to midwicket
just over mid-off. 145 kph, full delivery on off and middle. Smith backs away and lofts the ball calmly over mid-off. Not great timing but just enough.
145 kph, down the leg side, another wide. Runs leaking
on the pads this time, another poor delivery. 143 kph, worked to fine leg
147 kph, full outside off, Head wafts and is beaten on the outside edge
full, and outside off, hint of turn, push-driven into the covers for one
flatter, straying into the hips, whipped off to the left of deep midwicket. They press on for the second
tossed on middle and leg, much slower at 81.2ks, knocked more or less straight to midwicket
slides on middle, at least 10ks faster than the previous ball, hit down the ground, the bowler scampers to his left to stop the ball
full, straight ball on middle, Head hangs back and glides a single to cover
pushed through wider outside off, and Smith happily drives it down to long-off for a jogged single
144ks short and outside off, hip-high delivery, sits up, swat-pulled away to the right of midwicket

back of a length and angled in, 140.5ks, Smith gets inside the line and glances it fine on the leg side. He races across for the second. Raises his bat and celebrates his first ODI ton v New Zealand. Takes in the applause from his home crowd
144.1ks, dug short and angled down leg, Smith swerves inside the line. Pace can be your best friend. Pace can be your enemy too. Leg-side wide
back of a length and outside off, 120.2ks, slower and outside off, Smith waits patiently and plays a little checked-punch through the covers
whipped away off the hips to deep midwicket
very full and outside off, 143ks, Smith is right forward to meet the pitch of the ball. Driven su-weetly, but extra cover throws himself to his left to stop the ball
110ks slower bouncer outside off, bit of tennis-ball bounce, Smith leaves it be
fired flatter and just a shade outside off, Head camps back and forces it back to Santner

Australia chance a quick single. Umpire Dharmasena shakes his head, suggesting Smith is in. The TV umpire confirms it: Smith is in. New Zealand needed a direct hit to get Smith, who dishes out a full-length dive. The throw from mid-off was a bit wide from the stumps. Head skipped out of the crease, drilled it to mid-off, and set off. Smith responded, his bat also got jarred in the turf, but had enough time to recover
flatter and quicker, whipped to the right of midwicket
tucked away to midwicket
slides on the hips, worked to midwicket's left
tossed up slower on middle, defended
141ks, short and slanted across off, swish and a miss
much fuller and outside off, Head brings out his carving knife and slices it over the covers
slower delivery, pretty full on middle and leg, bunted to midwicket
overpitched and outside off, shovel-driven with immense authority, just to the left of the bowler. Fifth boundary for the left-hander
119ks slower one on the pads, Head spots it, waits for the ball to arrive and then works it behind square. No violence here
shorter and angled in at off stump, Smith swivels back and pulls it in the air over square leg. There is a man patrolling the boundary
arm-ball slides in with the arm. Smith whips a single through square leg
94ks, flighted on middle, driven down the ground to long-on for one. Head moves to 49
uses his feet, gets closer to the pitch, and deliberately chips it in the air over midwicket. There is a man in the deep
clipped off the hips through square leg. Head collects a half-century in his first ODI at home
Smith shuffles across, takes a straight ball, and twirls it through midwicket
95ks, hurled in, fizzes off the surface, no turn. Pings the front pad of Head as he eyes a leg-side flick. He weathers the lbw appeal, as it pitched outside leg
back of a length and outside off, Smith invests in a back-foot force square through the off side
length and slanting away outside off, Head carves it out to deep point
forceful whip from Smith. Full and on off, Smith, having moved across off, hits it in the air to the right of the square leg umpire
banged in short and outside off, Smith pulls firmly to the left of de Grandhomme, who is about 20 metres in from the boundary. Good fielding from de Grandhomme, but Smith still picked off two
very full and straight, Smith's wrists have more work to do. Flicked away to deep midwicket
full and angling away outside off, Head hammers a drive down to long-off. He attempted to over-hit the ball and lost his shape on it

Boult returns and finds a way past Smith and Head. He dives to his right from his follow-through and plucks out a smart, low catch with both hands. Full and angled in on off, possibly stopped a bit on the left-hander. He pushes in the air, and ends up lobbing a return catch. Excellent reflex catch
short and angled in from over the wicket, helped fine of long leg
good length and outside off, pushed into the off side
short and outside off, jabbed with hard hands to point
dug outside off, controls a back-foot pull to deep midwicket
back of a length on off, dabbed to cover. Smith is interested in a single, Wade sends him back
nice and full outside off, handsomely driven to deep cover
very full and angling away outside off, drilled away to sweeper cover

slower short ball outside off, 115.2ks, Smith chances a second. He dishes out a full-length dive again, this looks closer; he is home again. He spotted the lack of pace, skipped back and pulled it away to deep midwicket's right
that's an early Christmas present from Ferguson. Full-toss outside off, think the slower ball went awry. Very awry. Front-foot no-ball. Punches it crisply to the right of extra cover
and Smith capitalises on the free-hit.  Backs away outside leg, opens up his hips, and creams it inside out over extra cover. Lofted hit. Away she sails over the rope
very full on off, whipped with the wrists to midwicket
short on leg stump, cramps Wade for room. Miscues the pull, gets it fine of long leg
banged in short and angling away outside off, Smith attempts a hook and top-edges the ball over square leg. Latham runs back and mops it up
back of a length on middle and leg, whipped to midwicket
short and sits up outside off, flat-bats a cut to sweeper
full and wide outside off, Smith likes it there, crunches a drive through the cover-point region

slower ball, picked up and dispatched. Buh-bye ball. 115ks offering on the pads, Smith spots it, and flicks it smartly over backward square leg for another six. Fine leg is inside the circle, and no protection in the deep
full on middle and leg, possibly another slower one, worked away to square leg. Smith retains the strike
starts off with what looks like a slower offcutter, worked away to fine leg
Wade joins the party in Sydney. Shortish on middle, Wade camps back and pull-swings it, baseball style into the stands beyond midwicket
length and outside off, flat-batted powerfully down the ground, Santner dives full-length to his left from mid-off to intercept it
very, very wristy again. Pitched up on off, chipped in the air over midwicket
and Wade sends Neesham into the stands beyond wide long-on now. Another slower one outside off, Wade hangs back and clobbers it away. 300 is definitely on

this is even better. Wade scoops a six over fine leg. Follows the violent blows with finesse. Full toss on middle, Wade pre-meditated. Goes low and shovels it, Smith enjoyed that too. 21 runs off the over, and 52 runs off the last three overs
massive six. Back of a length and outside off, pulled away into the stands beyond square leg
too full on middle and leg, whipped away to the right of deep midwicket

Smith celebrates his 150, and what a shot to bring up the landmark. Very full and angling away outside off, opens the face late and manipulates it very fine of short third man. This is now his best score in ODI cricket

Munro was wrong-footed, he dives late to his right, and attempts the catch with both hands, and just finger-tips it away. Pretty full and just a shade outside off, whipped in the air, the ball just flew of the bat, and Munro messed it up. New Zealand's fielding has let them down today
Wade uses his feet and forces the ball to square leg
very full, drilled down the ground. Australia have plundered 67 runs off the last four overs
short ball on middle, 121.7ks, swats it with a flat bat to wide long-on. The throw from the deep is wild, very wide of the stumps, the keeper can't collect the ball. Smith hares across for the second
slower bouncer outside off, below head-height, Smith has a swat at it early, and does not connect. Not called a wide
Smith races down the track, takes a half-volley, and belts it through the covers, to the left of a diving mid-off. The ball is flying away in Sydney
slower short ball, swatted to midwicket
118.3ks short ball, flapped in the air over square leg
hip-high short ball, pulled away, short fine leg dives to his left and keeps it to a single
very full and wide outside off, past the tramline. Wide called. Boult smiles wryly, 300 up for Aus
very full on off, whipped away to wide long-on. Smith passes AB's 162, he is now has the highest ODI score at the SCG

Munro hangs onto a skier, Smith walks back to a standing ovation. Rousing reception for Smith from his home crowd. Williamson, Santner, and Guptill also congratulate Smith on his landmark. Back of a length and outside off, Smith has a hack at it, skews it in the air with the bottom hand flying off the bat. Munro was probably late again, he moves to his left from square leg and completes a diving catch at the midwicket region. Smith exits with 164, the highest individual ODI score at the SCG
slower cutter, 110ks, Wade slogs early and takes it on the pad
full on the stumps, hammered down the ground
swish and a miss outside off

someone finally nails a yorker, inside-edged behind square. Farcical fielding from NZ. The fielder at short fine leg collects the ball and has a wild throw, the ball goes towards cover (for a left-hander). Wade spots it, and aims for the second. Cummins isn't interested. The fielder at cover throws the ball at the non-striker's end, where Boult fumbles. Wade is safe and he collects two
dug short and outside off, clubbed away over midwicket
Wade pre-meditates, aims a fine scoop, but this is pretty full and outside off. He checks his shot and drills it through the covers on his knees
hacked down to mid-off off the inside half

Wade attempts another scoop, he only deflects it onto the stumps. Nice and full, outside off. Wade, having shuffled across, can't get enough bat on it. The zing bails go flying. He was looking to play it fine of fine leg, who had been brought up
back of a length and outside off, Starc punches it to the covers
full and outside off, sliced away to the right of sweeper cover
very full on the pads, picked up and flicked in the air over square leg, no protection in the deep
114.6ks, slower full delivery outside off, Starc picks it up and launches it straight down the ground. One-bounce four

polite appeal for caught behind from Watling. Given out by umpire Martell. Did the brush the glove on its way? Or just the helmet? Starc challenges the on-field decision. Big bouncer on middle, the batsman was late on the hook. Grazes the top edge, then the helmet and then flies into the gloves of Watling down the leg side. Hotspot detects a white blotch on the bat and the helmet. Snicko picks up a spike too as the bat meets the ball
back of a length and outside off, punched in the air over the covers
wide yorker outside off, Zampa shuffles across, swishes, and is beaten. Very close to being called a wide
lovely start. 142 kph, full on middle. The ball moves back in and Guptill defends towards mid-on
146 kph, full and swinging again. But sliding down leg. Guptill misses a flick and is struck on the pad
nice flowing drive. 145 kph, full outside off, thrashed to extra cover
146 kph, full and straight from Starc. Lovely lines, defended back
149 kph, clips the pad on its way to the keeper. Strays down leg again does Starc
149.7 kph, overpitched outside off from Starc. Guptill drives to extra cover. Maiden to start
lovely start. Full and swinging back in, 140 kph, worked through square leg for a couple. Got bat down in time
full and wide, 143 kph. Too wide outside off and called
138 ks. Close to off outside off, nice channel. Left alone by Latham
141 kph, overpitched outside off, Latham goes after it but the ball misses the outside edge. Just a hint of lateral movement
good length outside off, left alone
138 kph, nice and close to off from Hazlewood, defended into the off side

gone! Another early wicket for Australia. Latham chops on. Good length outside off, fifth-stump channel. Latham looks to prod one into the off side but the ball moves back late. Takes the inside edge and clatters into the stumps. Another opening batsman undone by just a hint of lateral movement. Well bowled Hazlewood
full outside off, defended into the off side
good length outside off, 145 kph. Guptill stays in the crease and defends to point. Lovely line
146 kph, full on off, a hint of inward movement. Pushed to mid-off
a nervous block. Fullish length close to off, Guptill gets forward and looks to defend. Tentatively plays it into his body
lovely stroke. 146 kph, full and straight. Guptill plants his front foot forward and lofts the ball neatly over mid-on. Doesn't bother keeping it down.
superb follow-up. 149 kph, searing yorker on middle and leg. Guptill does well to keep it out
quality single. Full outside off, swinging away. Williamson pushes into the off side for quick run
full and straight, 138 kph, pushed to mid-on
lovely from Guptill. Full delivery around off, Guptill backs away, makes a bit of room and lofts the ball straight over the bowler's head. Sublime stroke-making.
141 kph, good length on middle and leg, pushed to mid-on from the crease
135 kph, good length outside off, pushed out towards cover from the crease
good length on off, 137 kph, blocked.
good length outside off, 146 kph, left alone by Williamson
close to off with a full length. Defended into the off side
nice channel. 146 kph, good length on a sixth-stump line. Williamson dabs towards backward point
full outside off again, slightly wider of the crease. Defended
superb shot. Back of a length outside off, Williamson gets on top of the bounce, got both his feet off the ground at point of impact and cut the ball over point.
148 kph, good length around off, defended
on the pads, worked away through backward square leg for a couple. Good shot again
full delivery outside off, skewed off the outside half to point
139 kph, good length on the pads, nudged away to mid-on
another good single. Just tapped into the leg side, towards mid-on for a quick run
139 kph, overpitched on off, driven to mid-on
nice and full outside off, left alone by Williamson. Good over
shot! Another six. Just a flick of the wrists. Full and straight, aided by some inward movement. Guptill whips the ball off his pads over the deep square leg boundary
full and straight again, driven through cover. Warner chases it down from mid-off
uppish, short of point. Back of a length outside off, Williamson looks to cut but the ball skews off the outside half and falls just short of Bailey at backward point
151 kph, full on off, driven to mid-off
delightful. 147 kph, overpitched on off. Williamson drives the ball past his partner. Superb straight drive
147 kph, full and straight, defended. Good over
141 kph, drifts down leg, wide
142 kph, good length outside off, the ball comes back in. Guided to point from the crease
good length on the pads, 135 kph, worked to midwicket for a run
140 kph, overpitched outside off, driven to short cover
full outside off, 139 kph, solidly defended

gone. Huge wicket. Williamson nicks off. Full outside off, the ball holds its shape. Williamson goes after it, looking to drive through the off side. Gets a thick outside edge which carries at head height to Smith at first slip who takes a sharp reverse-cupped catch. NZ lose their best batsman.
143 kph, back of a length on off, defended into the off side
125 kph, close to off, left alone
126 kph, keeps it outside off with a full length. Left alone too
131 kph, overpitched outside off, drilled to long-off for one
angled across the left-hander on a good length, no stroke offered
nicely played. 129 kph, overpitched on off, sweetly driven back past Guptill for three to mid-off. Full face of the bat
128 kph, another quick single. Good length outside off, pushed to mid-on. Sets off immediately
139 kph, full on off, driven to mid-off
135 kph, good length outside off, swerving back in. Punched to extra cover from the crease
on the pads and flicked away through midwicket for one
140 kph, on the pads and Neesham flicks away through midwicket for four. Lovely shot. Putting away the bad ball
beauty. Full delivery outside off, 139 kph, the ball moves away late and beats the bat. Lovely bowling
138 kph, full on off, shovelled to square leg
130 kph, full and straight, defended
full outside off, 131 kph, driven to the deep cover fielder
134 kph, overpitched outside off, driven back to the bowler
135 kph, full and wide from Marsh. Neesham throws his hands at that but misses
good length outside off, played into the off side
131 kph, impeccable channel just outside off, Neesham defends into the off side
superb shot. Back of a length outside off, the ball sits up for Guptill, Hammered to the deep cover boundary with a swat off the front foot
141 kph, glided to backward point from the crease
145 kph, overpitched on middle, worked away into the gap at midwicket with ease. Strays on the pads. Not a good delivery
better. Good length outside off, pushed to cover
good length on off, defended into the off side
four more. Short and wide outside off, Guptill laces his cut and finds the gap behind point for four. Another great stroke
132 kph, full on off, worked into the leg side
full on a sixth-stump line, caressed to extra cover from the crease
just a push to Warner at mid-on for one, good single
short and wide outside off, slapped in front of cover for a run
ah, should have done more with that. Short and wide outside off, scythed to extra cover
another lovely lofted drive. Full on the fourth stump from Marsh, Neesham calmly lifts his checked drive over mid-o. The ball lands just in front of the boundary cushion before popping up off it
143 kph, full and wide from Cummins. With the extra pace, the ball flies off the bat. Guptill flays and sends the ball whistling past point for four
good riposte. Back of a length at 144 kph, Guptill sways away from the line
short and wide, 142 kph. Guptill wants to cut over point but can't make contact. Nice idea, just lacking in execution
shortish and wide outside off, slashed to deep point
just wide of him. Impossible to catch them, just have to stick. Strays on the pads and flicked just past Bailey at short leg
excellent bouncer. Well-directed. Guptill gets underneath that and lets it go. Good stuff
shortish and wide outside off, swatted to long-on with a drag
84 kph, slow outside off, punched to long-off
84 kph, slow through the air but a bit leg side-ish too, off the pad to square leg
89 kph, flat on off and middle, worked to midwicket
shortish and flat, drilled down to long-on
95 kph, quicker through the air, straight and full and pushed to cover
146.2ks head-high bouncer on the leg stump, Neesham sinks under it
chest-high short ball on middle, swatted away to long leg
short and wide outside off, 145ks, it probably went faster to the boundary. Rasping cut, sends it to the square boundary. Becomes the quickest NZ player to 5000 ODI runs
147.5ks, good length and outside off, push-driven to the covers
pretty full on off, nearly 148ks, Guptill presses forward and drives the ball to mid-on
back of a length on off, 145.9ks, tapped to extra cover
flatter on middle and leg, hangs back and whips to square leg
pushed through quicker, Neesham has a big slog-sweep across the line and does not connect. It clearly pitched outside leg
googly, but Zampa goes short, pulled away to deep midwicket
short skidder on middle, stays back and pulls down to long-on
slower through the air on middle, chipped in the air, Warner runs in and attacks the ball from long-on, but it lands in front of him
very full on middle, 146ks, Neesham is on the move as he shovels it away wide of mid-on
veering into the hips, 147.3ks, the batsman is late onto the flick. Off the high and rolls square through the leg side
much fuller and angled in on off, Guptill glides it to third man and raises his fifty off 55 balls
full and outside off, throws his hands at it with no feet and slices an outside edge down to third man
lifter outside off, 144ks, Guptill arches back and ramps it smartly over the top of Smith at first slip. One-bounce four
length and outside off, Guptill takes it on the up and middles a drive to the left of mid-off
straight ball on middle, driven down to long-off
shorter and outside off, punched on the back foot to long-on
slides on quick outside off, back-foot force to extra cover
tossed slower on middle, pushed back to the bowler

Bailey at midwicket spills a tough catch, or at best a half-chance. Half-tracker outside off, Guptill rocks back and pummels a pull. Bailey attempts the catch with both hands, but he was late on it. That was a rocket from Guptill. Bursts through the hands of the fielder
shorter and outside off, chopped away in the gap at backward point
good length on middle, squirted to midwicket off the inside edge
back of a length and outside off, nearly 148ks, Neesham looks to cut and ends up skewing it towards point off the inside half. Hustled for pace
clears long-on. Length ball on off, Neesham hangs back and swings it over the fielder with a straight bat. Much like a short-arm jab
beats mid-off (Cummins) to his left. Half-volley outside off, belted down the ground. Boom
Starc pulls his length back on middle, Neesham leaps off his feet and fends it onto the pitch
pitched up and outside off, sliced in the air over the covers
full on middle, gets forward and taps it to the left of the bowler
tossed-up legbreak outside off, Guptill backs away outside leg and chips it inside out over extra cover. Long-off moves to his left to collect the ball
rank half-tracker outside off, goes back and unleashes a rasping pull to the right of Bailey at midwicket, beats Travis Head at deep square leg to his left
flighted legbreak outside off, Guptill likes the width and marmalises a six over extra cover. Just skimmed off the middle of the bat. Clears the long boundary with some nonchalance
tossed on the stumps, driven along the ground to extra cover
straight just outside off, driven firmly to long-off
overpitched and outside off, drilled to extra cover

full and slanting away outside off, Guptill goes hard on a drive and slices an outside edge past the outstretched right hand of point. Head runs across to his left in the deep, dives, his hand was in contact with the ad board while collecting the ball. Another four for Guptill
short and skids in, 144.6ks, extra bounce pings the glove
good length and outside off, punched on the up to mid-off

Neesham holes out to Hazlewood at wide long-on. Good length and outside off,  Neesham has a clean swing at the ball. But can't clear the long boundary. Hazlewood runs to his left and pouches it. Starc returns and breaks the 92-run stand
banged in short on the leg stump, hops and fends the ball to square leg
dropped short and outside off, slapped away to sweeper cover
shorter legbreak outside off, beats Watling's attempted cut
tossed on middle, presses forward and defends it back to the bowler
low full-toss on middle, paddled fine of long leg
short and turning away, leans back and punches through cover
too short on middle, Guptill is quick to read the length. Nimbly skips back and bludgeons a pull over midwicket
full, and angled in just outside off, squeezed to cover
wide of the crease, 145.8ks, straightens away a bit outside off, Watling chases an expansive drive and does not connect
wide of the crease and angled into a front-foot push to mid-on
full and cuts away outside off, dabbed to point
very full and on off, driven straight to cover on the front foot
full and holds its line outside off, Watling drives to sweeper cover and picks up a single
short and just outside off, cramps the batsman for room. Played back to the bowler
spooned over the head of Warner, running back and to his left from mid-off. Good length and outside off, Watling plays early, chips, and escapes

whoa, Smith has pulled off a stunning catch. He flies to his left like a goalkeeper and completes an incredible one-handed catch. Lands face-first, but tucks the ball up against his ribs, and hangs on. Smith's team-mates jump onto him. This was a poor ball, though - short and wide outside off - Watling cuts hard, but can't keep it down. It seemed destined to fly off to the boundary until Smith took flight and intervened at backward point. Smith plucks it out with his wrong hand. He barely had any time to react. He is having a banner day at the SCG. Even Smith is surprised by that catch
back of a length on middle, defended
length and outside off, jabbing punch to deep cover
short and angling across off, guided to point
back of a length and outside off, swish and a miss
short and angled in, angled to backward point
short and just outside off, hops and glides it down to third man
very full and outside off, shovel-driven to extra cover, who dives to his left and deflects the ball to mid-off

Munro chases the long boundary and just clears Head at the edge of the boundary. Good length and outside off, swung away in the air.  Head runs across to his right from deep midwicket, dives full-length, and finger-tips it over the boundary. Even if he had caught it, he would have landed outside the ad boards
short and outside off, cut firmly to sweeper cover
back of a length and outside off, punched to point
length and outside off, stabbed away square on the off side
back of a length and outside off, chopped behind to the keeper via a bottom edge
just short of a good length and outside off, baseball-swings it into the stands beyond wide long-on
push-driven down to long-off
back of a length on middle, punched to extra cover
back of a length and angled in, solidly defended back to the bowler
short and outside off, gets on top of it and rides it down to third man
back of a length and outside off, punches and skews an outside edge to third man
back of a length and outside off, punched to the right of extra cover
short and angled in at the ribs, leaps and steers the ball down to fine leg
too straight in line, picked off to deep midwicket
back of a length and outside off, front-foot punch back to the bowler
good length and and angled in on middle, worked to midwicket
back of a length on off and middle, cramps him for room. Chopped to point
back of a length and angled in, the batsman misses the leg-side flick. Flies off the inside of the front thigh into backward point's hands
back of a length and swerves in, pushed back to Marsh
back of a length on off, crams Munro up for room. Stabbed back to the bowler. Rare maiden
back of a length, angled in, straightens away outside off past the skittish poke of Guptill
full on off, pushed in the air to the left of the bowler to mid-off
back of a length on off, chopped behind to superman Smith. Nine dots in a row
back of a length on off, late-cut away, can't beat Smith at backward point. 10 dots in a row
short and angled in, cramps him for room. Worked in front of midwicket for a quick one
full and wide outside off, half-volley, stabbed only as far as mid-off
good length and outside off, driven fine of backward point
back of a length and outside off, stands tall and punches straight to mid-off
full and outside off, lashed on the front foot to extra cover
short and angled in just a shade outside off, forced down to long-off. Munro gets a run after nine balls
what a way to bring up a century. This is a Guptill special; so easy on the eye. Fullish and outside off, nonchalantly launched over long-on for a six
good length and outside off, punched down to long-off
length and angled into leg stump, rolls off the thigh fine on the leg side
back of a length and veers in on off, Guptill aims to drive through the off side, ends up squirting an inside edge down to long-on
back of a length on off, pushed to point. The pressure on Munro rises
full and angling away outside off, the left-hander looks to drive, and gets an outside edge, which does not carry to Steven Smith, who had moved from midwicket to slip before this ball
back of a length and outside off, punched crisply to sweeper cover for one
back of a length, chopped from off stump fine of backward point
starts off with a short one outside off, cracked away to backward point, who dives and takes some pace off the ball
slower through the air, legbreak, which dips late in its flight, inside-edged to midwicket
tossed on middle, little chip over the bowler's head. Guptill and Munro hare across for two

Finch races in from sweeper cover, attacks the ball, as opposed to staying back and protecting the boundary. The ball lands in front of him and rolls away to the boundary. Slower legbreak outside off, some extra spin, Guptill aims to drive and ends up slicing it in the air. He gets away
fuller and quicker on middle, defended

Guptill has hit a dirty long hop to midwicket. Maxwell leaps, and takes the overhead catch on the second attempt. Guptill drops to his knees in despair. Dragged short and outside off, skids on Guptill pulls it flat and hard. Finds the substitute fielder
length and angling away outside off, jabbed away to the right of extra cover
short and moving across the left-hander, skirting past the outside edge
full on off, Santner does not move his feet much. Played back to the bowler
back of a length and seaming away outside off, beats the outside edge lavishly again
and again. Good length and zipping away outside off, past the nervy prod
good length and curling away outside off, Santner has a flirt before drawing his bat inside the line
skids into the pads, misses the flick
tossed up just outside leg, worked away behind square
looped up on leg stump, nearly spooned back to the bowler

holes out to Warner at long-on. Dolly catch. With two wickets in five balls, Zampa has tilted it Australia's way. Tossed-up legbreak on off, dips late in its flight. Santner lofts it half-heartedly, the bat turns in his hands, and picks out Warner to perfection, who blows a kiss and celebrates the catch
pitched up on off, flicked to midwicket
skidding into the pads, flicked square through the leg side
back of a length and angling away outside off, dabbed to the right of extra cover for one
full and breaks back into de Grandhomme, chopped to the covers
full and moves in, inside-edged onto the pad. The ball rolls towards square leg
back of a length and outside off, mowed over the bowler's head. Swatted away with a flat-bat. That's Munro's second boundary, and his first since the 26th over
guided towards backward point
good length and ducks back in, pops an inside edge near where short midwicket would have been
short on middle, leans back and outside leg as he punches to sweeper cover

skids on flat and just outside off, beats the batsman, nearly shaves the off stump. Stumping chance sent upstairs,bounces over the off stump. Wade swipes the bails off. De Grandhomme's back foot is grounded
down the track, takes a full ball and stabs it to the right of the bowler
use his feet and drills a straight drive
looped up on middle and leg, nurdled to midwicket
short and wide outside off, beats the cut
Wade takes it in front of his head. Sharp bouncer on middle and leg, Munro ducks under it
slog-swept away to deep midwicket
full and just outside off, whipped in the air over wide mid-on

very full, and cuts in, de Grandhomme is stapled to the crease as he plays across the line. The ball skids on to rap his front pad plumb in front of middle.  No signs of an inside edge. Umpire Dharmasena's finger goes up. The batsman reviews more out of hope rather than conviction. He has no hope at all. Horrid review. Three reds flash, and New Zealand are seven down
141.8ks, yorker, hoops in sharply, Henry is late to jam his bat down, inside-edged past the leg stump to the left of the keeper
pretty full on off, Henry hangs back and flat-bats it powerfully through the covers
three boundaries in a row for NZ. Tossed up outside off, hammered away over extra cover
skidding into the pads, turns, misses the flick
legbreak on middle and leg, backs away and lofts it over mid-off, who is up
dragged down on leg stump, punched down to long-on

tossed up and drifts in to hit the back pad in front of leg stump, not sure if straightened enough. Zampa gestures it was heading down leg, but Australia challenge the not-out on-field call from Martell, and review. No inside edge, and ball tracking detects it was pitching outside leg.
looped up and outside off, lofts at this legbreak, and slices it in front of Warner tearing in from long-off
back of a length and slanting away outside off, Munro has a massive mow and does not connect
full-toss on off, driven to sweeper cover
just short of a good length on middle, flat-batted to midwicket
back of a length and bounces over the stumps as Henry backs away, swishes wildly, and does not make contact
back of a length and outside off, flat-bats a drive and finds mid-off
length ball on off, Henry eyes a leg-side swipe, the ball takes a thick outside edge and rolls down to the third man fence
reverse swept from off stump to backward square leg
tossed up outside off, slog-swept over wide long-on for a six, caught in the crowd
full and fired on middle, hacks at it, and sends an inside edge to long leg
full and outside off, poked to point
pushed through on off, turns, Munro does not connect with a reverse-sweep
googly turns away outside off, pushed into the covers
very full and angled in, inside-edged to fine leg

Munro's bat is broken. One part flies over cover, the other over midwicket. Very full and outside off, he throws his hands at a drive and secures a single. Munro has the part of the bat with just the handle. Bizarre play. The impact was near the bottom of the bat
back of a length on middle, slogged away to deep midwicket
off-side wide
tucked away square of short fine leg, Marsh runs around the ball, chases, then makes a mess of the slide, the batsman gets four. Marsh just dragged the ball along with him to the boundary boards
Munro plays it to midwicket and sets off. A direct hit from Warner could have dismissed him
length ball on middle, clears his front leg and meatily clubs it away for a one-bounce four to long-on
full and wide outside off, slashes a drive to sweeper cover
114.2ks slower one outside off, swish and a miss
even slower, 113ks, guided to short third man
slower bouncer on middle, 110ks, half-ducks under it
short and slow outside off, 111.6ks, slapped away to sweeper cover's right
wide yorker outside off, too wide, according to the umpire. Henry reaches out and does not connect
fuller and outside off, possibly slower, wild swing and a miss
short and outside off, sits up, shovel-pulled away to deep midwicket

full and outside off, right in the hitting slot. Henry clears his front leg and swipes the slower one in the air. He plays early. He gets more height as opposed to distance. Bailey runs in from deep midwicket and tracks down the skier. First wicket for Cummins on return
very full and wide outside off, carved down to third man
very full and slants in, takes the pad and wanders away through square leg

Bailey tracks down another skier. This is tougher. He moves about 30 metres to his left from extra cover and pouches it near the mid-off region. Slower full ball outside off, Munro slogs and holes out for 49
full and curves in, inside-edged onto the pad
slower full toss on off, clipped away to midwicket

Chopped on. Australia go 1-0 up. The middle stump is pegged back. Back of a length and slanted in, Ferguson aims to force it through the off side. Ends up playing it on. He bags a three-ball duck on international debut
